<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1439,2005]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Head, polished, slightly wider than pronotum. Crown about half as long medially as pronotum. Pronotum polished, longer than combined length of scutum and scutellum, upper surface convex, transversely wrinkled.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="118" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1439,2005]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis box="[199,363,1548,1573]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<collectingCountry box="[199,257,1548,1573]" name="Malta" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Male</collectingCountry>
genitalia
</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[377,435,1548,1573]" name="Malta" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Male</collectingCountry>
pygofer posteriorly conically rounded with macrosetae confined to posterior 
<number box="[1301,1350,1548,1572]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" value="0.33">0.33</number>
region. Valve 
<taxonomicName box="[224,335,1583,1608]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangular">triangular</taxonomicName>
, about twice as broad at base as medially long, posteriorly narrowed with rounded apex, lateral margins sinuate. Subgenital plate with well developed membranous apical process 
<number box="[1123,1172,1620,1645]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" value="0.36">0.36</number>
times as long as total length. Style with well developed lateral subapical lobe, apophyses straight, transversely rugose. Connective with stem shorter than arms. Aedeagus with shafts elongate, simple, diverging in ventral view and curved dorsally in lateral view, with small 
<taxonomicName box="[428,537,1727,1752]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangular">triangular</taxonomicName>
lobe at midlength along inner margin visible both in ventral and lateral view; gonopore apical on ventral margin; ventral process in lateral view with strongly sinuate ventral margin immediately distad of midlength, 
<number box="[389,424,1800,1824]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" value="2.2">2.2</number>
times as long as shaft, tapering to acute apex, with small 
<taxonomicName box="[1093,1202,1799,1824]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangular">triangular</taxonomicName>
lamellate expansion dorsally immediately distad of midlength.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1439,2005]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis box="[199,395,1871,1896]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Seventh sternite 
<number box="[611,646,1872,1896]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" value="1.7">1.7</number>
times as wide basally as long medially; posterior margin concave laterally and medially produced into lobe with median short V-shaped excavation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1439,2005]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis box="[199,361,1945,1968]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Measurements</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[377,435,1944,1969]" name="Malta" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Male</collectingCountry>
<quantity box="[444,531,1944,1969]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[606,694,1944,1968]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes. Female 4.0 mm long and 
<quantity box="[1206,1294,1944,1968]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="17" pageNumber="118" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
