<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="119" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,260,285]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[323,410,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Litura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unda">
<emphasis box="[323,410,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">L. unda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from the 
<typeStatus box="[691,789,260,285]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">holotype</typeStatus>
male and 
<typeStatus box="[908,1016,261,285]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">paratypes</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1086,1197,260,285]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
(not examined); it is recorded here for the first time from 
<collectingCountry box="[559,620,295,320]" name="India" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">India</collectingCountry>
. Both 
<taxonomicName box="[691,776,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Litura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unda">
<emphasis box="[691,776,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">L. unda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[830,963,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Litura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangula">
<emphasis box="[830,963,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">L. triangula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very similar in coloration. 
<taxonomicName box="[1307,1392,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Litura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unda">
<emphasis box="[1307,1392,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">L. unda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has more a convex thorax and is more slender compared to more robust 
<taxonomicName box="[985,1135,332,357]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangular">
<emphasis box="[985,1135,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">L. triangular</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which has relatively flat pronotum. The females have rather similar seventh sternites, however, the median lobe is more prominently produced posteriorly in 
<taxonomicName box="[419,504,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Litura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unda">
<emphasis box="[419,504,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">L. unda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
compared to 
<taxonomicName box="[658,791,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Litura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangula">
<emphasis box="[658,791,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">L. triangula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
